<title type="html"><![CDATA[What Is The Ruling On Taking Bay’ah – Shaykh Saalih Al-Fawzaan]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="https://forum.salafiri.com/viewtopic.php?t=420&amp;p=449#p449"><![CDATA[
Shaykh Saalih Al-Fawzaan was asked…<br /><br /><strong><span style="color: #0000FF">Q: What is the ruling on taking Bay’ah for the (different) groups like that of the muslim brotherhood? Is this from splitting and leaving the Jamaa’ah (the Congregation of the Muslims)?</span></strong><br /><br />A: Bay’ah is given to the Muslim ruler. It is not to be given to other than the Muslim ruler. It is not to be given to the president of a group, or the leader of a group. Rather it is only to be given to the general Muslim ruler, yes.<br /><br />Translated from: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://www.alfawzan.af.org.sa/node/14239">http://www.alfawzan.af.org.sa/node/14239</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Translator: Muhammad Abouharb<br /><br />Source: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://albinaapublishing.com/what-is-the-ruling-on-taking-bayah-shaykh-saalih-al-fawzaan/">http://albinaapublishing.com/what-is-th ... l-fawzaan/</a><!-- m --><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="https://forum.salafiri.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=56">Shehzad Sattar</a> — Mon Sep 19, 2016 12:30 am</p><hr />
